YELLOW PINE CO., Respondent, v. KANE, Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. May 12, 1893.) Action by the Yellow Pine Company against Thomas Kane for an injunction restraining the commencement of summary proceedings to remove defendant from leased lands. On motion of plaintiff, an order was made continuing an injunction, and defendant appeals. Affirmed.

Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. J., and FOLLETT and BARRETT, JJ.

Townsend & Mahan, for appellant. Jackson & Burr, (J. A. Burr, Jr., of counsel,) for respondent PER CURIAM.

The order must be affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements.
